President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate Ashley Jay Elizabeth Poling of North Carolina to be a Commissioner of the Postal Regulatory Commission. Poling currently serves as the Director of Governmental Affairs and Senior Counsel for Senator Gary C. Peters, where she advises on policy issues, negotiates bipartisan legislation, and develops initiatives. She has previous experience working as Senior Policy Counsel to Senator Heidi Heitkamp and as Counsel to Senator Jon Tester, focusing on postal and federal workforce issues. Poling has bipartisan relationships with postal stakeholders and is a native of North Carolina. She is a graduate of the College of William & Mary and the Elon University School of Law.